VEHICLE_CLASSES <- c(

EMFAC2014 estimates

Our first step is to construct EMFAC_VMT_data: a table providing estimates of (daily) VMT for any given year, county, speed, and fleet mix.

We consider LHDT2, MHDT, HHDT classes (EMFAC2014) and TRUCK (in our traffic data) to be equivalent.

decode_speed_indexes <- function (.data, bins = MPH_BINS) {
  speed_levels <- 5 * seq_along(bins)
  speed_labels <- bins
  .data %>%
    mutate(speed = ordered(speed, speed_levels, speed_labels)) %>%
    ensure(!any(is.na(.$speed)))
}
standardize_EMFAC_variables <- function (.data) {
  preferred <- c(year = "CalYr", speed = "Speed", fuel = "Fuel",
                 pollutant = "Pollutant", mode = "Mode", 
                 veh_class = "VehClass")
  .data %>%
    rename_(.dots = preferred[na.omit(match(names(.data), preferred))]) %>%
    mutate(county = decode(Region, DST_COUNTY_REGIONS, warn = FALSE)) %>% 
    select(-Region)
}
EMFAC_VMT_data <-
  EMFAC2014_speedwise_data %>%
  filter(VMT > 0) %>%
  standardize_EMFAC_variables() %>%
  decode_speed_indexes() %>%
  select(county, year, veh_class, speed, fuel, VMT) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  group_by(year, speed, county, fuel,
           fleet = ifelse(veh_class %in% TRUCK_CLASSES[[layer_name]], 
                          yes = "TRUCK", no = "NON")) %>%
  total_each(VMT) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  with_comment("VMT from EMFAC2014-v1.07 (RUNEX only).")
set.seed(1)

add_geom_bar <- function (.vis, ...) {
  .vis + geom_bar(..., stat = "identity", position = "identity")
}

add_VMT_scale <- function (.vis, limits, ...) {
  if (missing(limits)) {
    max_observed_VMT <- max(.vis$data$VMT, na.rm = TRUE)
    limits <- c(0, max(1e6, round(max_observed_VMT, digits = -6)))
  }
  .vis + scale_y_continuous("VMT/day", limits = limits, labels = format_SI, ...)
}

add_MPH_scale <- function (.vis, ..., limits = c(0, 70), breaks = seq(5, 75, by = 20)) {
  .vis + scale_x_continuous("Speed (mph)", ..., limits = limits, breaks = breaks)
}

Satisifed with the alignment of the speedwise distributions (???), we construct composite traffic_emission_factors by simply taking the VMT-weighted averages of the factors in the speedwise_RUNEX_data and speedwise_VMT_data (that we harvested from EMFAC2014).

We do this by speed, fuel, and fleet, as well as by county and year.

It’s possible that we are trading too much bias for variance here — it might be better to smooth across different ranges (or the entire range of) speed. Or to smooth along other/additional dimensions!

speedwise_emission_tbl <-
  EMFAC2014_speedwise_data %>% 
  standardize_EMFAC_variables() %>%
  decode_speed_indexes() %>%
  group_by(year, speed, county, fuel, pollutant, mode,
           fleet = ifelse(veh_class %in% TRUCK_CLASSES[[layer_name]], 
                          yes = "TRUCK", no = "NON")) %>%
  summarise(Tons = total(Tons), # weighted.mean(Rate, w = VMT), 
            VMT = total(VMT)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  spread(pollutant, Tons, fill = NA) %>%
  select(year, county, fleet, fuel, mode, speed, everything()) %>%
  with_comment("Daily emissions and VMT by year, county, fleet, fuel, mode, speed, and pollutant.")
tripwise_emission_tbl <-

  group_by(year, county, fuel, pollutant, mode,
           fleet = ifelse(veh_class %in% TRUCK_CLASSES[[layer_name]],

  summarise(Tons = total(Tons), #weighted.mean(Rate, w = VMT), 
            VMT = total(VMT)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  spread(pollutant, Tons, fill = NA) %>%
  select(year, county, fleet, fuel, mode, everything()) %>%

Fuel fractions

The missing bits (in the shapefile-based traffic data) are the fuel breakdowns (conditional on fleet and speed). If it had that, we’d be able to align our models at a more detailed/granular level.

Since it’s missing, we’ll impute fuel fractions by using statistics calculated from the EMFAC2014 data. Specifically, we’ll estimate the fraction of VMT attributable to a given fuel (e.g. DSL or GAS) among vehicles of a given fleet traveling at a given speed within a given year and county.

This might be trading too much bias for variance — we might want to smooth over speed or fleet when we estimate these fuel_fractions.

fractions_of_VMT_by <- function (.data, ..., fill = 0.0) {
  totaled <- .data %>% group_by(..., add = TRUE) %>% summarise(VMT = total(VMT)) 
  fractions <- totaled %>% mutate(VMT = VMT / total(VMT)) 
  fractions %>% spread(..., VMT, fill = fill)
} 

# ELEC, but no speeds
tripwise_fuel_fractions <-
  filter(tripwise_emission_tbl, mode == "TOTAL") %>%
  group_by(county, year, fleet) %>%
  fractions_of_VMT_by(fuel)

# no ELEC (but does have speeds)
speedwise_fuel_fractions <-
  speedwise_emission_tbl %>%
  ensure(all_true(.$mode == "RUNEX")) %>%
  group_by(county, year, speed, fleet) %>%
  fractions_of_VMT_by(fuel)

III. Link-level emissions

For each link, we apportion the VMT from traffic_volumes using both (a) tripwise_fuel_fractions or (a) speedwise_fuel_fractions, for the purposes of calculating contributions from (a) brake & tire wear, as well as (b) running losses (evaporation) and exhaust.

Then we use emission_factors to estimate daily emissions of each pollutant attributable to each link from **wear*, running losses, and exhaust.

Finally, we add in contributions from road dust, apportioned by xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx.

We store the per-link emission estimates in a column called ems_qty (g/day), indexed by lnk_id, county, year, speed, fleet, fuel, and pollutant. (We’ll use these results very soon to rescale our “tracer concentrations” — computed on a per-link basis — before summing the contributions from multiple links to individual receptors).

As a bit of QA/QC, we construct and use a helper function called ensure_emissions_total to verify a few subtotals right at the end.

# For on-the-fly verification of emission subtotal(s) 
ensure_emissions_total <- function (.data, .pol, .year, qty, unit, ...) {
  filtered <- filter(.data, year == .year, pollutant == .pol)
  stopifnot(all(filtered$ems_unit == unit))
  stopifnot(all.equal(total(filtered$ems_qty), qty, ...))
  return(.data)
}
# Let `apply_fractions` be the same thing as `apply_scalars`.
# (Just makes it easier to read the intent of our code.)
apply_fractions <- inventory::apply_scalars
EMFAC_POLLUTANTS <- c("CO", "CO2", "NOx", "PM10", "PM2.5", "ROG", "TOG", "SOx")

Tire and brake wear (PM2.5 only)

WEAR_MODES <- c("PMTW", "PMBW")

wear_rate_tbl <- 
  tripwise_emission_tbl %>%
  filter(mode %in% WEAR_MODES) %>%
  select(-one_of(setdiff(EMFAC_POLLUTANTS, "PM2.5"))) %>%
  mutate_each(funs(. / VMT * GRAMS_PER_TON), PM2.5) %>%
  select(-VMT) %>%
  spread(mode, PM2.5) %>%
  with_comment("Tripwise emission rates (g/veh-mi). Basis: EMFAC2014-v1.07")

lnk_wear_emissions <-
  traffic_volumes %>%
  select(county, lnk_id, year, speed, fleet, VMT) %>%
  apply_fractions(tripwise_fuel_fractions, "VMT", "fuel") %>% # apportion (State Highway) speedwise VMT by (EMFAC) speedwise fuel fraction
  apply_scalars(wear_rate_tbl, "VMT") %>%  # multiply VMT by emission factors
  gather(mode, ems_qty, one_of(WEAR_MODES)) %>%
  mutate(pollutant = "PM2.5") %>%
  mutate(ems_unit = "g/day") %>%
  filter(ems_qty > 0)

lnk_wear_emissions %>%
  filter(lnk_id == "L0", year == SAMPLE_YEAR)

  read_csv() %>%
  mutate(county = decode(Region, DST_COUNTY_REGIONS, warn = FALSE)) %>% 
  select(county, matches("^PM")) %>%
  gather(metric, `g/VMT`, -county) %>%
  mutate(metric = str_uppercase(metric)) %>%
  extract(metric, into = c("mode", "fleet", "fuel"), regex = "PM2_5_([A-Z]+)_([A-Z]+)_([A-Z]+)_ER") %>%
  spread(mode, `g/VMT`)

lnk_dust_emissions <-
  traffic_volumes %>%
  select(county, lnk_id, year, speed, fleet, VMT) %>%
  apply_fractions(tripwise_fuel_fractions, "VMT", "fuel") %>% # apportion (State Highway) speedwise VMT by (EMFAC) speedwise fuel fraction
  apply_scalars(dust_rate_tbl, "VMT") %>%  # multiply VMT by emission factors
  gather(mode, ems_qty, PMRD) %>%
  mutate(pollutant = "PM2.5") %>%
  mutate(ems_unit = "g/day") %>%
  filter(ems_qty > 0)

lnk_dust_emissions %>%
  filter(lnk_id == "L0", year == SAMPLE_YEAR)

lnk_length_data <-
  lnk_centerlines@data %>%
  select(lnk_id, lnk_length = MILES)

which_pollutant <- "PM2.5"

map_data <- 
  lnk_emission_data %>%
  filter(year == SAMPLE_YEAR) %>%
  filter(pollutant == which_pollutant) %>%
  annual_emissions_by(lnk_id, speed, pollutant, fleet) %>%
  left_join(lnk_length_data) %>%
  mutate(ems_rate = ems_qty / lnk_length) %>%
  select(-ems_qty) %>%
  spread(fleet, ems_rate) %>%
  mutate(ALL = TRUCK + NON)
## Joining by: "lnk_id"
# Join to `lnk_centerlines` and reproject to (lon, lat)
map_layer <-
  merge_SpatialDataFrame(lnk_centerlines, map_data, by = "lnk_id") %>%
  reproject(WGS84)

popup_default <- function (...) str_c("<p>", ..., "</p>")
popup_for_link <- function (lnk_id, speed, ALL, TRUCK) {
  sprintf("<p><b>Link %s</b> </br> %s MPH</p> <p><b>%s (per day):</b> <br/> ALL: %0.0f g/mi </br> TRUCK: %0.0f g/mi</p>",
          lnk_id, speed, which_pollutant, ALL, TRUCK)
}

# Render a nice map
leaflet(map_layer) %>%
  addProviderTiles('CartoDB.Positron') %>% 
  addPolylines(weight = ~(ALL / 300), 
               color = gray(0.3), opacity = 1.0,
               popup = ~popup_for_link(lnk_id, speed, ALL, TRUCK)) %>%
  addPolylines(weight = ~(TRUCK / 300), 
               color = "orange", opacity = 1.0,
               popup = ~popup_for_link(lnk_id, speed, ALL, TRUCK))

Finally, we save lnk_emission_data, fuel_fractions, and emission_factors — along with the previously constructed link_geom and traffic_volumes — in the file highway_emissions.Rda.

write_csv(
  tripwise_fuel_fractions %>% mutate_each(funs(round(., digits = 5)), DSL, ELEC, GAS), 
  build_path(layer_name, prefixed("fuel_fractions-tripwise.csv")))

  speedwise_fuel_fractions %>% mutate_each(funs(round(., digits = 5)), DSL, GAS), 
  build_path(layer_name, prefixed("fuel_fractions-speedwise.csv")))

  build_path(layer_name, prefixed("emission_factors-exhaust.csv")))
  
write_csv(

  build_path(layer_name, prefixed("emission_factors-runloss.csv")))

  build_path(layer_name, prefixed("emission_factors-wear.csv")))

  build_path(layer_name, prefixed("emission_factors-dust.csv")))
